Sure thing! Here's a function that takes an array of 5 numbers, checks if each number is a prime number, and prints any prime numbers to the console:

```
function checkForPrimes(arr) {
  for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    let isPrime = true;
    for (let j = 2; j <= Math.sqrt(arr[i]); j++) {
      if (arr[i] % j === 0) {
        isPrime = false;
        break;
      }
    }
    if (isPrime && arr[i] > 1) {
      console.log(arr[i]);
    }
  }
}
``` 

You can call this function with an array of 5 numbers like this: `checkForPrimes([2, 4, 7, 10, 11]);` and it will print any prime numbers in the array to the console.
